All Classes

Class Description
Board
Board represents the game's board, containing all Square data in a grid.
Card
Card represents a playing card in the game Murder Madness.
Computer
Computer is a subclass of Player describing an autonomous Player.
Estate
Estate is a subclass of Card, describing an estate in Murder Madness.
Estate.Name
All Estate names.
Estate.Side
All sides of an Estate.
EstateSquare
EstateSquare is a subclass of Square, representing a square within an Estate.
Game
Game class is the main class of Murder Madness, containing all game data and representing the current game state.
GameCharacter
GameCharacter is a subclass of Card and represents a playable character in Murder Madness.
GameCharacter.Name
All GameCharacter names:
GameConfigurationDialog
GameConfigurationDialog is a customized JDialog that uses JRadioButtons and JTextFields to let Players choose their character and type their nickname.
GameTests
GameTests contains a list of tests that cover the Murder Madness program.
GuessOptionPane
GuessOptionPane is a JOptionPane with JRadioButtons that allows Players to make a guess/solve attempt by selecting a Card of each applicable type.
GUI
GUI initiates and controls the display of the user interface.
GUI.DrawPanel  
GUI.TextPanel
TextPanel is a custom JPanel on that displays important text during the game.
InputPanel
InputPanel is a custom JPanel.
NormalSquare
NormalSquare is a subclass of Square representing the majority of squares on the board.
Player
Player describes a player in the game Murder Madness.
RefuteOptionPane
RefuteOptionPane is a custom JOptionPane that uses a JComboBox to allow a refuting Player to choose which Card they would like to refute.
Square
Square is an abstract class representing each square on the Board of Murder Madness.
WallSquare
WallSquare is a subclass of Square, representing a Square that GameCharacters can't be placed on.
Weapon
Weapon is a subclass of Card representing a weapon card.
Weapon.Name
Al Weapon names:
